<TITLE> Crash kills NTV journalist, 2 others </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, July 26 (bdnews24.com)A road crash on the Rangpur-Bogra highway early on Sunday killed three people including a private television channel reporter, police said. Abdur Rashid, Kotwali police chief said, as NTV's Rangpur reporter Litu Anam, Rangpur Kotwali sub-inspector Raihan and others were travelling from Rangpur to Bogra by car early Sunday. An oncoming truck hit their vehicle head-on at Bahubal of Shibganj killing Doctors' Clinic owner Ashikuzzaman Shimu of Rangpur and the driver Opu on the spot. Critically injured Litu Anam and the police officer were admitted to Rangpur Medical College Hospital, where Litu died at 11:30am. 
